                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="425068" author="dongyang" created="Tue, 20 Aug 2024 00:56:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andreas, we already have SB_I_STABLE_WRITES on the superblock,&lt;br/&gt;
the problem is when doing buffered IO via raw block device, not going through filesystem, there&apos;s no filesystem superblock yet,&lt;br/&gt;
and it really is a kernel bug fix that should be backported to the rhel releases.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="425052" author="adilger" created="Mon, 19 Aug 2024 23:06:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dongyang&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dongyang&quot;&gt;dongyang&lt;/a&gt;, I was looking at these kernel patches, and I wonder if it would be possible to implement them in osd-ldiskfs/ or ofd/ to set the &lt;tt&gt;SB_I_STABLE_WRITES&lt;/tt&gt; on the superblock rather than doing it on a per-mapping basis?  This would avoid the need for a kernel patch, since all of the callers that are checking the disk queue or inode mapping are already checking if the superblock has the &lt;tt&gt;SB_I_STABLE_WRITES&lt;/tt&gt; flag set.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="408820" author="pjones" created="Sat, 23 Mar 2024 15:20:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.16&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="408768" author="gerrit" created="Sat, 23 Mar 2024 05:53:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Oleg Drokin &amp;lt;green@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/52922/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/52922/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
